Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{a glug}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Tip: Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(halved and chopped into 6 wedges). Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed), quarter lengthways and then chop into roughly 5cm long batons. Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved, core removed and sliced into 1cm wide strips). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Put the @British chicken breasts{2} in a #bowl{} with a glug of oil and half the @dried thyme{1}(half). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Massage the seasoning into your chicken.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Pop the red onion, carrot and pepper on a baking tray. Sprinkle on the remaining dried thyme, add a glug of oil and season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat the veggies then roast in your oven until soft and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). Lay in the chicken breasts and cook until browned on both sides, about ~{2-3%minutes} each side. Once browned, transfer to your baking tray on top of the veggies and cook for the remaining ~{15-20%minutes}.

> Important: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Don't wash your pan - you need it again in a minute!

Whilst the chicken is roasting, add the @chicken stock powder{1} and @water{100}(for the sauce) to the chicken frying pan, bring to a boil then reduce the heat to a simmer. Add the @fresh chilli jam{1} and bubble the mixture until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once cooked, remove the chicken, veg and wedges from your oven. Slice each chicken breast into five slices. Combine the wedges, vegetables and chopped parsley together on one of the #baking trays{}, then spoon onto plates. Arrange the chicken on top and reheat the sweet chilli glaze if needed. Spoon the sweet chilli glaze over the chicken and enjoy!